: \n418: ### Phase 11: Documentation\n419: \n420: - [ ] **DOC-001**: Create `cmd/cli/README.md`\n421:   - Package overview\n422:   - Installation instructions\n423:   - Quick start guide\n424:   - Usage examples\n425: \n426: - [ ] **DOC-002**: Add docstrings to all public classes and methods\n427:   - PackRuntime class and methods\n428:   - MetadataService class and methods\n429:   - AgentMetadata model\n430:   - MetadataOptions dataclass\n431: \n432: - [ ] **DOC-003**: Create `cmd/cli/examples/README.md`\n433:   - Document example agents\n434:   - Include pack command examples\n435: \n436: ### Phase 12: Build & Test Configuration\n437: \n438: - [ ] **BUILD-001**: Verify pyproject.toml pytest configuration\n439:   - Set testpaths = [\"tests\"]\n440:   - Set asyncio_mode = \"auto\"\n441: \n442: - [ ] **BUILD-002**: Verify pyproject.toml ruff configuration\n443:   - Set line-length = 100\n444:   - Set target-version = \"py310\"\n445: \n446: - [ ] **BUILD-003**: Verify pyproject.toml mypy configuration\n447:   - Set python_version = \"3.10\"\n448:   - Set strict = true\n449: \n450: ## Acceptance Criteria\n451: \n452: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube --version` prints version and exits\n453: - [ ] `kubectl-agentcube pack` command accepts all specified options\n454: - [ ] Workspace validation works for Python (requires .py files) and Java (requires pom.xml)\n455: - [ ] Metadata loading falls back through filenames (agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml)\n456: - [ ] Metadata saves to agent_metadata.yaml in correct YAML format\n457: - [ ] CLI option overrides apply to metadata\n458: - [ ] Dockerfile generation works for Python agents\n459: - [ ] Dockerfile generation works for Java agents\n460: - [ ] Entrypoint inference works from workspace files\n461: - [ ] Verbose error handling shows traceback\n462: - [ ] Rich progress spinner displays during pack operation\n463: - [ ] Unit tests achieve >= 80% code coverage\n464: - [ ] Package installs via `pip install -e .`\n465: - [ ] Example agents pack successfully\n466: - [ ] Pydantic validators reject invalid language/build_mode/port values\n467: - [ ] All files have corresponding _test.go files (for .py files: _test.py pattern via test_*.py)\n468: \n469: ## Dependencies\n470: \n471: | Dependency | Source | Usage |\n472: |------------|--------|-------|\n473: | `typer[all]` | External (>=0.9.0) | CLI framework with Rich support |\n474: | `pydantic` | External (>=2.0.0) | Data validation with BaseModel |\n475: | `pyyaml` | External (>=6.0) | YAML parsing and dumping |\n476: | `httpx` | External (>=0.24.0) | HTTP client (future commands) |\n477: | `docker` | External (>=6.0.0) | Docker SDK (future commands) |\n478: | `rich` | External (>=13.0.0) | Terminal formatting |\n479: | `packaging` | External (>=23.0) | Version parsing |\n480: | `importlib-resources` | External (>=6.0.0) | Resource file access |\n481: | `semver` | External (>=3.0.0) | Semantic versioning |\n482: | `pytest` | External (>=7.4.0) | Testing framework |\n483: | `pytest-asyncio` | External (>=0.21.0) | Async test support |\n484: | `pytest-cov` | External (>=4.1.0) | Coverage reporting |\n485: | `pytest-mock` | External (>=3.11.0) | Mocking utilities |\n486: | `httpx-mock` | External (>=0.10.0) | HTTP mocking |\n487: | cli-toolkit/spec.md | Internal | CLI specification |\n488: | cli-toolkit/design.md | Internal | CLI design |\n489: | python-sdk/design.md | Internal | Python SDK design |\n490: \n491: ## Implementation Order\n492: \n493: ```\n494: TASK-001 → TASK-009 (Package structure)\n495:     ↓\n496: TASK-010 → TASK-021 (Metadata models)\n497:     ↓\n498: TASK-030 → TASK-032 (Metadata options)\n499:     ↓\n500: TASK-040 → TASK-058 (PackRuntime)\n501:     ↓\n502: TASK-060 → TASK-063 (Runtime stubs)\n503:     ↓\n504: TASK-070 → TASK-072 (Service stubs)\n505:     ↓\n506: TASK-080 → TASK-085 (CLI main)\n507:     ↓\n508: TASK-090 → TASK-093 (Example agents)\n509:     ↓\n510: TEST-001 → TEST-026 (Tests & fixtures)\n511:     ↓\n512: DOC-001 → DOC-003 (Documentation)\n513:     ↓\n514: BUILD-001 → BUILD-003 (Build config)\n515: ```\n516: \n517: ## Coverage Verification\n518: \n519: - [ ] **COV-001**: Run coverage check\n520:   - Command: `pytest --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing tests/`\n521:   - Verify code coverage >= 80%\n522:   - Verify all .py files have corresponding test_*.py files\n523:   - Verify main logic paths covered\n524: \n525: ## File Structure\n526: \n527: ```\n528: cmd/cli/\n529: ├── pyproject.toml\n530: ├── README.md\n531: ├── agentcube/\n532: │   ├── __init__.py\n533: │   ├── cli/\n534: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n535: │   │   └── main.py\n536: │   ├── models/\n537: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n538: │   │   └── pack_models.py\n539: │   ├── runtime/\n540: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n541: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py\n542: │   │   ├── build_runtime.py\n543: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py\n544: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py\n545: │   │   └── status_runtime.py\n546: │   ├── services/\n547: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n548: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py\n549: │   │   ├── docker_service.py\n550: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py\n551: │   │   └── agentcube_provider.py\n552: │   └── operations/\n553: │       └── __init__.py\n554: ├── examples/\n555: │   ├── hello-agent/\n556: │   │   ├── main.py\n557: │   │   └── requirements.txt\n558: │   └── math-agent/\n559: │       ├── main.py\n560: │       └── requirements.txt\n561: └── tests/\n562:     ├── __init__.py\n563:     ├── conftest.py\n564:     ├── test_pack_runtime.py\n565:     ├── test_metadata_service.py\n566:     └── fixtures/\n567:         ├── __init__.py\n568:         ├── valid_python_agent/\n569:         │   ├── main.py\n570:         │   └── requirements.txt\n571:         └── valid_java_agent/\n572:             ├── pom.xml\n573:             └── src/main/java/App.java\n574: ```\n575: \n576: ## Command Reference\n577: \n578: ### pack Command\n579: \n580: ```bash\n581: kubectl-agentcube pack [OPTIONS]\n582: \n583: Options:\n584:   -f, --workspace PATH          Path to agent workspace directory [default: .]\n585:   --agent-name TEXT             Override agent name\n586:   --language TEXT               Programming language (python, java)\n587:   --entrypoint TEXT             Override entrypoint command\n588:   --port INTEGER                Port to expose in Dockerfile\n589:   --build-mode TEXT             Build strategy: local or cloud\n590:   --description TEXT            Agent description\n591:   --output PATH                 Output path for packaged workspace\n592:   --verbose                     Enable detailed logging\n593:   --help                        Show this message and exit\n594: ```\n595: \n596: ### Global Options\n597: \n598: ```bash\n599: kubectl-agentcube [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]\n600: \n601: Options:\n602:   --version                     Show version and exit\n603:   -v, --verbose                 Enable verbose output\n604:   --help                        Show this message and exit\n605: ```\n606: \n607: ### Example Usage\n608: \n609: ```bash\n610: # Pack Python agent with defaults\n611: kubectl-agentcube pack -f /path/to/agent\n612: \n613: # Pack with custom options\n614: kubectl-agentcube pack \\\n615:   --agent-name my-agent \\\n616:   --language python \\\n617:   --entrypoint \"python main.py\" \\\n618:   --port 8080 \\\n619:   --build-mode local \\\n620:   --output /tmp/packaged-agent\n621: \n622: # Pack with verbose output\n623: kubectl-agentcube pack -f ./my-agent --verbose\n624: ```\n625: \n626: ## Testing Strategy\n627: \n628: ### Unit Tests\n629: \n630: 1. **PackRuntime Tests**: Validate packaging logic, workspace validation, metadata handling\n631: 2. **MetadataService Tests**: Validate metadata loading, saving, validation\n632: 3. **Model Tests**: Validate Pydantic validators and dataclass behavior\n633: \n634: ### Integration Tests\n635: \n636: 1. **test_pack_hello_agent**: Full pack flow with hello-agent example\n637: 2. **test_pack_math_agent**: Full pack flow with math-agent example\n638: 3. **test_pack_with_output_path**: Pack with custom output path\n639: 4. **test_pack_java_agent**: Pack Java workspace (when fixture available)\n640: \n641: ### Test Fixtures\n642: \n643: - `valid_python_agent/`: Python workspace with main.py and requirements.txt\n644: - `valid_java_agent/`: Java workspace with pom.xml and src/\n\n(End of file - total 644 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020 — CLI Pack Command Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-020 — CLI pack 命令 |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-3 completed |\n\n## Atomic Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: Package Structure Setup\n\n- [ ] **TASK-001**: Create `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`\n  - Define build system (setuptools>=61.0, wheel)\n  - Set project metadata (name, version, description, license, authors)\n  - Specify Python requirement (>=3.10)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775866499005,"end":1775866499028}}}}
